name: Royal Chess — Strategické šachy
description: Co se stane, když v šachové hře figurky ožijí? Jak se šachy změní, když střelci potřebují k boji šípy?

manifest.author: mrklas
manifest.lore: The pieces have been alive for as long as anyone can remember. They bleed when struck, tire when marching too far, and hunger between battles. Every pawn dreams of the last rank. Every king dreads the silence before check. The board is not a battlefield — it is a world, and its inhabitants know it.

entities.name: Off Board
entities.description: The graveyard. Captured pieces reside here; their remains are used to recycle the very rare ivory.

entities.name: d1
entities.description: White queen's home square. Back-rank safety — pieces here recover endurance.

entities.name: f1
entities.description: White light-archer's home square. Back-rank safety — pieces here recover endurance.

entities.name: h8
entities.description: Far corner of the 8th rank. Deep in black territory. The rook cut off all escape — but holding here is exhausting.

entities.name: White King
entities.description: The white sovereign. Moves one step in any direction — never into danger. The game ends when he falls.

entities.name: White Queen
entities.description: The most powerful piece. Moves in all 8 directions, any distance. Exhausted from the last assault — retreated to d1 to recharge.

entities.name: White a-Rook
entities.description: Stationed at the a-file corner, awaiting the endgame. Patient, powerful, built for open files.

entities.name: White b-Knight
entities.description: Bold opener — leaps over the pawn wall before the game has begun.

entities.name: White c-Archer
entities.description: Dark-squared archer. Prowls the long black diagonals from c1, never touching a light square.

entities.name: White f-Archer
entities.description: Light-footed archer. Ranges across diagonals, never crossing to dark squares. Barely survived the last exchange — back on f1 with a sliver of strength, quiver nearly empty.

entities.name: White g-Knight
entities.description: Classical kingside opener. Leaps over pawns and lands with a threat.

entities.name: White h-Rook
entities.description: The rook that dared the 8th rank. Controls the entire row — but every tick in enemy territory drains its endurance.

entities.name: Black King
entities.description: The black sovereign. Sheltered deep in his own ranks — for now. Every tick the enemy presses closer.

entities.name: Black Queen
entities.description: The black queen surveys the board from d8, ready to strike the moment white overextends.

entities.name: Black a-Rook
entities.description: Anchored at a8. Waits for the queenside file to open.

entities.name: Black b-Knight
entities.description: Poised to challenge the centre. Quick and cunning.

entities.name: Black c-Archer
entities.description: Dark-squared black archer. Commands the long diagonal — patient and dangerous.

entities.name: Black f-Archer
entities.description: Light-squared black archer. Eyes the kingside from f8.

entities.name: Black g-Knight
entities.description: Kingside guardian. Quick to react to white aggression.

entities.name: Black h-Rook
entities.description: Fallen. Captured when white dared the 8th rank — now its ivory fuels the war effort from the graveyard.

entities.name: Black h-Pawn
entities.description: Black's last hope. Stranded on a6, racing toward promotion. Every tick counts.

entities.name: Arrows
entities.description: Required ammunition for archer fire. Each shot costs 1 arrow. Issued by the king; production can be delegated to other pieces. Can also be looted from captured enemy archers, or appear rarely on the board.

entities.name: Hay
entities.description: Basic fodder for horses. Each knight move costs 4 units of hay. Issued by the king; production can be delegated to pawns. Can be looted from enemy pawns or appear rarely on the board.

entities.name: Oats
entities.description: Energy fodder for horses. Each knight move costs 1 unit of oats. Issued by the king; production can be delegated to pawns. Can be looted from enemy pawns.

entities.name: Ivory
entities.description: Used to repair a destroyed board square. Each repair costs 1 unit. Obtained from captured pieces.

entities.name: Dynamite
entities.description: Explosive needed to destroy a board square. Each blast costs 1 unit. Cannot be crafted — appears rarely on board squares.

entities.name: Piece
entities.description: Any chess piece — a living participant in the battle, subject to endurance, capture, and resource constraints.

entities.name: King
entities.description: The sovereign. Moves one step in any direction. Its fall ends the game — protect it at all costs.

entities.name: Queen
entities.description: The supreme commander. Ranges freely in all 8 directions, any distance. The most powerful piece on the board.

entities.name: Rook
entities.description: The fortress tower. Commands open files and ranks with orthogonal reach. Strongest in the endgame.

entities.name: Knight
entities.description: The leaping warrior. Ignores all pieces in its path; strikes in an L-shaped arc. Unpredictable and nimble.

entities.name: Archer
entities.description: The diagonal ranger. Commands the long diagonals and never leaves its colour. Requires arrows to fight.

entities.name: Pawn
entities.description: The foot soldier. Slow, expendable — but every pawn carries a queen within.

entities.name: Chess Square
entities.description: One of the 64 squares of the board. Serves as a type anchor for location-based production rules.
